pulltitle: Repeat search until package is indexed
pullsbody: Two search tests test_search_by_addon_name_returns_addon and test_search_by_library_name_returns_library were failing sporadically with the constant sleep time of 10 seconds. This is due to the time between package creation and indexing by the search job being dependent upon a queue. Sometimes it can be <10 seconds but other time it can be up to 60 seconds or more. Devs and I considered this was still reasonable UX performance but adding a 60 second sleep into the test was not acceptable as it would lock out the grid node. Stephen and I did not want to lose or xfail this test coverage as we consider it valuable. This solution is to repeat the search until the timeout value is reached. I have used dynamic time loop to account for the implicit waits in Webdriver and make sure the timeout limit is adhered to properly. The method needs to re-load the search page during the while loop to avoid results caching. I have also addressed: - https://www.pivotaltracker.com/story/show/19392391 - search_for_term method - set is_displayed to a property as it should have been.
pull_commit_message:
Repeat search until package is indexed
Set is_displayed as a property

pulltitle: Add xfail to 2 search tests - see bug 695283

pullsbody:
Pull includes:

Search
test_search.py - Coverage for search functionality on FlightDeck

Teardown
Added a method to make a urllib connection and delete packages created during the test. Too much test data was being left in staging and causing problems.

The package IDs are logged from within the page object function that creates a new add-on or lib. This means that from within the test you only need to call delete_test_data() to remove any data, if any exist.
